WEBVTT

00:04.738 --> 00:05.706 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.739 --> 00:06.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.740 --> 00:08.542 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.575 --> 00:10.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
With no Democrat support, we
couldn't quite

00:10.077 --> 00:11.044 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
get there.

00:11.078 --> 00:13.313 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're just a very small number
of votes short.

00:13.347 --> 00:18.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In a defeat for
Republicans,
President Trump and House
Speaker Paul Ryan

00:18.952 --> 00:24.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pull the GOP's health care bill,
lacking the
votes needed to replace the
Affordable Care

00:24.658 --> 00:26.126 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Act.

00:26.159 --> 00:27.661 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And it's Friday.

00:27.694 --> 00:32.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mark Shields and David Brooks
are here to
analyze a packed week of news.

00:32.332 --> 00:37.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, Jeffrey Brown talks with
the director
of the sequel to the dark
comedy/drama hit

00:37.971 --> 00:42.342 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Trainspotting" about bringing
characters
back to life after 20 years.

00:42.376 --> 00:44.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANNY BOYLE, Director, "T2:
Trainspotting":
One of the joys of doing the
film was the

00:44.878 --> 00:51.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
learning process of seeing how
poorly men
age and how wise women are,
whereas we -- it's

00:51.585 --> 00:53.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not even like we think we're
living in the
past.

00:53.587 --> 00:56.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We just are, and we're not
admitting it to
ourselves for so long.

00:56.823 --> 01:04.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:04.298 --> 01:07.034 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:07.067 --> 01:17.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Republican
effort to replace
Obamacare, the health care law,
lies in ruins

01:17.878 --> 01:19.646 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tonight.

01:19.680 --> 01:24.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the 11th hour today, House
GOP leaders
gave up trying to hold a vote on
their bill.

01:24.184 --> 01:26.787 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our Lisa Desjardins has been at
the Capitol
all day.

01:26.820 --> 01:27.788 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She begins our coverage.

01:27.821 --> 01:29.089 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

01:29.122 --> 01:30.524 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: I
will not sugarcoat this.

01:30.557 --> 01:32.259 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is a disappointing day for
us.

01:32.292 --> 01:36.730 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: After a
dramatic week of
will they or won't they,
Republicans' selected

01:36.763 --> 01:42.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
won't, pulling their sweeping
health care
bill shortly before a scheduled
vote, when

01:42.102 --> 01:44.671 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it clearly was short of the
support it needed.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.473 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

01:46.506 --> 01:49.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Moving from an
opposition party
to a governing party comes with
growing pains.

01:49.543 --> 01:53.513 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, well, we're feeling those
growing pains
today.

01:53.547 --> 01:58.118 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We came really close today, but
we came up
short.

01:58.151 --> 02:01.054 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Doing big things is hard.

02:01.088 --> 02:05.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All of us, all of us, myself
included, we
will need time to reflect on how
we got to

02:05.726 --> 02:07.260 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this moment.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The House
speaker then acknowledged
the resulting reality.

02:09.096 --> 02:10.063 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:10.097 --> 02:11.365 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Obamacare is the law
of the land.

02:11.398 --> 02:14.001 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's going to remain the law of
the land until
it's replaced.

02:14.034 --> 02:17.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We did not have quite the votes
to replace
this law.

02:17.471 --> 02:20.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, yes, we're going to be
living with
Obamacare for the foreseeable
future.

02:20.507 --> 02:23.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Thank you very much.

02:23.377 --> 02:25.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We were very close, very, very
tight margins.

02:25.412 --> 02:29.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: President Trump
pointed to
a lack of Democratic votes and
said he's open

02:29.850 --> 02:31.618 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to discussing another bill.

02:31.651 --> 02:33.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, for now, health care will
stay as it
is.

02:33.920 --> 02:39.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I have been saying
for the last
year-and-a-half that the best
thing we can

02:39.893 --> 02:45.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
do, politically speaking, is let
Obamacare
explode, and it is exploding
right now.

02:45.432 --> 02:52.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This after a
wild 24 hours
of promises and pressure, with
Vice President

02:52.906 --> 02:57.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Pence meeting with the
conservative Freedom
Caucus today, and the White
House standing

02:57.377 --> 03:03.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by an ultimatum President Trump
issued last
night, that, if the bill failed,
he wouldn't

03:03.583 --> 03:05.252 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
return to the issue.

03:05.285 --> 03:06.920 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Press Secretary Sean Spicer
today:

03:06.953 --> 03:08.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
I know that the president's made
it clear

03:08.822 --> 03:12.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that this is the effort, this
was the train
that's leaving the station, and
that he expects

03:12.626 --> 03:14.895 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
everyone -- that this is our
opportunity.

03:14.928 --> 03:19.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Republicans
also dangled
some carrots, adding new changes
last night

03:19.433 --> 03:21.168 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to win votes.

03:21.201 --> 03:25.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For moderates, they revived a
Medicare tax
on the wealthy, using the
proceeds to help

03:25.305 --> 03:31.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
states increase health coverage,
and for conservatives,
a repeal of the Affordable Care
Act's guarantee

03:31.645 --> 03:37.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of basic, essential benefits,
things like
E.R. visits, prescriptions and
preventative

03:37.417 --> 03:38.552 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
care.

03:38.585 --> 03:41.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Removing the essential benefits
did sway some
members.

03:41.688 --> 03:42.789 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Joe Barton of Texas:

03:42.823 --> 03:44.591 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:44.624 --> 03:50.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOE BARTON (R), Texas: That is a
big win for
conservative values, so I am now
a yes vote.

03:50.764 --> 03:54.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Others refused
to budge,
including Barton's fellow Texan
Louie Gohmert.

03:54.868 --> 03:56.369 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:56.403 --> 03:57.237 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LOUIE GOHMERT (R), Texas: The
president shouldn't
give any more energy.

03:57.270 --> 03:58.238 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This was up to us.

03:58.271 --> 03:59.873 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It wasn't up to him.

03:59.906 --> 04:04.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm grateful that he spent
as much effort
trying as hard as he did.

04:04.778 --> 04:07.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: More no's came
from the ranks
of moderates.

04:07.447 --> 04:12.752 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The chair of House
appropriations, New Jersey's
Rodney Frelinghuysen, cited cuts
to Medicaid

04:12.786 --> 04:14.254 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
funding.

04:14.287 --> 04:17.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the White House, President
Trump said this
morning he has no regrets.

04:18.024 --> 04:20.060 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
QUESTION: Did you rush it, do
you think?

04:20.093 --> 04:22.028 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: We will see what
happens.

04:22.062 --> 04:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Mr. Trump also
said he had
full faith in Speaker Ryan
moving forward.

04:26.266 --> 04:31.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, by early afternoon, Ryan
was at the White
House, delivering the grim news
on the bill's

04:31.638 --> 04:32.839 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
prospects.

04:32.873 --> 04:35.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrats, meanwhile, pointed to
the Republicans'
disunity.

04:35.575 --> 04:37.277 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:37.310 --> 04:39.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), House
Minority Leader:
I think their mistake really was
they were

04:39.312 --> 04:45.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so focused on embarrassing the
Affordable
Care Act, rather than trying to
improve it.

04:45.552 --> 04:49.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Three months
into their control
of government, Republicans have
a central

04:49.823 --> 04:54.728 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
political and policy platform to
rebuild.

04:54.761 --> 04:56.596 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And this is a seismic moment.

04:56.630 --> 05:02.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Speaker Ryan says, nonetheless,
he's moving
to the next big mountain to
climb, tax reform,

05:02.068 --> 05:05.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
even though accomplishing tax
reform will
now be harder, Judy, because
they don't have

05:05.872 --> 05:08.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the savings that he was hoping
for from health
care reform.

05:09.009 --> 05:12.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Lisa, a lot
of finger-pointing
going on.

05:12.612 --> 05:17.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What is your reading from
talking to all the
people you have talked to about
why they couldn't

05:17.484 --> 05:19.252 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
get this done?

05:19.286 --> 05:20.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Yes, I want to
try and set
aside all the blame game --
there is a lot

05:21.021 --> 05:22.756 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of that -- and focus on three
things.

05:22.789 --> 05:26.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One, I just talked to Chairman
Greg Walden,
who was one of the co-authors of
this bill.

05:26.526 --> 05:31.331 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He said he felt that the
goalposts kept moving
from conservatives and
moderates, that they

05:31.364 --> 05:33.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
would give them one thing, and
then they would
ask for more.

05:34.000 --> 05:35.869 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's one factor.

05:35.902 --> 05:40.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Another, Republicans have a very
large conference,
but with that also comes large
differences

05:40.140 --> 05:42.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in policy, and they couldn't
bridge those.

05:42.042 --> 05:44.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The third, Judy, the timeline, I
think, was
a very big factor.

05:44.978 --> 05:49.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Republicans shot for the
moon here trying
to pass a massive bill in just
three weeks.

05:49.649 --> 05:53.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That didn't leave any breathing
room for very
serious concerns.

05:53.153 --> 05:54.955 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's why I think we saw
this bill fail.

05:54.988 --> 05:59.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Lisa, what
are Republicans
saying about what they think the
implications

05:59.159 --> 06:00.894 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are for their party, for them?

06:00.927 --> 06:04.264 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: They're worried
about 2018.

06:04.297 --> 06:09.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Democrats would need a sweep to
retake the
House, but for the first time, I
had two different

06:09.336 --> 06:12.872 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republican members tell me today
they're worried
that that sweep is possible.

06:12.906 --> 06:17.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's not just about their
individual elections,
Judy, but this takes the kind of
air out,

06:17.811 --> 06:21.715 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
all the energy out from
conservative causes
across the board.

06:21.748 --> 06:27.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have been campaigning on
this up and
down, nonprofits, politicians,
for seven years,

06:27.087 --> 06:30.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and they're just not sure where
the energy
now is going to come from for
all of these

06:30.924 --> 06:34.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
groups that have been pushing
for conservative
causes for years.

06:34.160 --> 06:37.063 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And just quickly,
what about
Speaker Ryan himself?

06:37.097 --> 06:38.398 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How is he affected by this?

06:38.431 --> 06:41.668 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I actually
think Speaker
Ryan is doing OK.

06:41.701 --> 06:45.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our Julie Percha, producer up
here, spoke
to several members of the
Freedom Caucus who

06:45.739 --> 06:48.174 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had nothing but good things to
say about Speaker
Ryan.

06:48.208 --> 06:52.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also, in his benefit, Judy, it
doesn't look
like anyone else wants his job
right now.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.847 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Hmm.

06:53.880 --> 06:54.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's interesting.

06:54.881 --> 06:55.849 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
All right.

06:55.882 --> 06:58.752 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins at the Capitol,
we thank you.

06:58.785 --> 07:01.388 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And now a view from the White
House today.

07:01.421 --> 07:05.892 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
