Washington Post
interviewed the president as the
bill was

07:05.925 --> 07:08.028 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
being pulled from consideration.

07:08.061 --> 07:10.196 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Robert joins me now in the
studio.

07:10.230 --> 07:12.632 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Robert, the president called
your cell phone.

07:12.666 --> 07:13.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What did he say?

07:13.667 --> 07:14.634 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA, The Washington
Post: Yes.

07:14.668 --> 07:15.635 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
He did.

07:15.669 --> 07:16.636 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was sitting over here in
Arlington.

07:16.670 --> 07:17.637 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was a blocked number.

07:17.671 --> 07:18.638 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And he got right to the point.

07:18.672 --> 07:20.840 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said, "Bob, I'm pulling the
bill."

07:20.874 --> 07:22.842 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he had just met with House
Speaker Ryan.

07:22.876 --> 07:25.078 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he said the votes weren't
there.

07:25.111 --> 07:29.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My whip count had about three
dozen Republicans
who were probably not going to
back the measure,

07:29.916 --> 07:32.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but he said it was closer, about
five to 12
votes away.

07:32.352 --> 07:33.820 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he said he's ready to move
on.

07:33.853 --> 07:36.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's going to not hold the bill
for a few
days.

07:36.323 --> 07:38.825 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's going to wait, in his
words, to let it
explode.

07:38.858 --> 07:44.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: He said in his
remarks to the
group of reporters, the
so-called pool there

07:44.764 --> 07:49.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the Oval Office, he said that
it's going
to be -- the next move is up to
the Democrats.

07:49.669 --> 07:54.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is that your sense of what
they're looking
for, or are they just shoving it
to the side

07:54.574 --> 07:55.775 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
now?

07:55.809 --> 07:57.544 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: He seems to be
open to a bipartisan
deal.

07:57.577 --> 07:59.346 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will see if that actually
emerges.

07:59.379 --> 08:04.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I said, you're kind of a
non-ideological
president, even though you're a
Republican.

08:04.384 --> 08:07.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Maybe you're more natural down
the road doing
something with the Democrats.

08:07.520 --> 08:10.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said, a lot of people may say
that, and
he said it with a chuckle.

08:10.390 --> 08:13.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But whether the Democrats would
be willing
to work with the president, we
will have to

08:13.526 --> 08:14.494 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
see.

08:14.527 --> 08:15.495 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I thought it was striking,
though.

08:15.528 --> 08:17.130 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He was pretty even-tempered.

08:17.163 --> 08:18.264 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
