18:02.248 --> 18:03.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are prepared to do that?

18:03.349 --> 18:05.051 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

18:05.084 --> 18:07.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIM RYAN: Well, I don't speak on
behalf of
my entire party, but I know I'm
willing to

18:07.119 --> 18:10.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sit down and say, look, we have
made some
great strides.

18:11.023 --> 18:12.358 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There are some issues.

18:12.391 --> 18:14.160 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Let's sit down and fix them.

18:14.193 --> 18:17.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have raised my hand to say,
I'm all in to
try to make sure that health
care is more

18:17.496 --> 18:19.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
affordable for more people, that
it's more
accessible.

18:19.832 --> 18:24.036 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We should have universal
coverage and that
should be affordable for
everybody.

18:24.070 --> 18:25.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here's the thing, Judy.

18:25.404 --> 18:27.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I hope Republicans would be
willing to
sit down and do it.

18:27.573 --> 18:30.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have been complaining about
Obamacare
for seven years.

18:30.309 --> 18:33.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They get into power, and their
first legislative
initiative, they can't even pass
something

18:33.879 --> 18:37.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that is an attempt to fix it,
but that was
because it was making it worse,
I think, was

18:37.950 --> 18:39.151 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
why it didn't pass.

18:39.185 --> 18:40.152 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But here's the thing.

18:40.186 --> 18:41.754 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're the United States of
America.

18:41.787 --> 18:44.056 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're the wealthiest country in
the world.

18:44.090 --> 18:47.059 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And yet we're 37th in health
care delivery.

18:47.093 --> 18:51.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We spend 2.5 times what other
developed countries
spend on health care.

18:51.731 --> 18:54.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Clearly, we're not doing
everything right.

18:54.166 --> 18:56.335 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We need to move more of that
money into prevention.

18:56.369 --> 18:58.471 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need to make sure that our
citizens are
healthier.

18:58.504 --> 19:02.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We got to have a big national
conversation
about our food system.

19:02.274 --> 19:04.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is how we're going to solve
the problem
in the long run.

19:04.577 --> 19:08.381 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, when
President Trump says
this was due to -- that this is
really the

19:08.414 --> 19:10.883 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Democrats' fault, what's your
answer?

19:10.916 --> 19:11.884 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

19:11.917 --> 19:13.452 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

19:13.486 --> 19:15.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM RYAN: Well, we're not even
in the majority
in the House of Representatives.

19:15.321 --> 19:17.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, how could it possibly be
our fault?

19:18.024 --> 19:21.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has complete control of the
House of Representatives.

19:21.527 --> 19:22.728 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They're all Republicans.

19:22.762 --> 19:25.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he couldn't even get the
Republicans to
pass it.

19:25.998 --> 19:27.767 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it's typical Donald Trump.

19:27.800 --> 19:31.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's going to find somebody to
blame, and
so he's going to blame the
Democrats.

19:31.337 --> 19:36.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I assume he's going to blame
President Obama
and maybe even Hillary Clinton
for this problem.

19:36.776 --> 19:38.511 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They need to take
responsibility.

19:38.544 --> 19:42.648 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They need to put a plan forward
that their
members can vote on and that
actually solve

19:42.681 --> 19:44.517 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
problems.

19:44.550 --> 19:47.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem right now with the
Republican
Party, Judy, is they're living
by bumper sticker

19:47.420 --> 19:48.387 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
slogans.

19:48.421 --> 19:49.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But now they're not in the
minority.

19:49.522 --> 19:51.323 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're in the majority now.

19:51.357 --> 19:55.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The dog has actually caught the
car, and they
got to figure out how to govern
the country.

19:55.361 --> 19:59.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Representative
Tim Ryan, we
thank you for talking with us.

19:59.165 --> 20:00.132 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

20:00.166 --> 20:01.767 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TIM RYAN: Thanks for having me.

20:01.801 --> 20:04.136 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next, for an
opposing perspective,
I am joined by Lanhee Chen.

20:04.170 --> 20:09.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is a fellow at the Hoover
Institution who
advised Mitt Romney and Marco
Rubio in their

20:09.241 --> 20:10.543 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
presidential campaigns.

20:10.576 --> 20:13.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lanhee Chen, welcome back to the
program.

20:13.179 --> 20:14.847 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What's your reaction to what
happened today?

20:14.880 --> 20:16.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LANHEE CHEN, Former Policy
Director, Mitt
Romney Campaign: Well, thank
you, Judy.

20:16.549 --> 20:19.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think this is clearly a
self-inflected wound
for Republicans.

20:19.418 --> 20:24.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They had the opportunity to move
ahead on
really the only train out of
town, if you

20:24.523 --> 20:28.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will, to repeal the Affordable
Care Act and
replace it with some other
reforms.

20:28.394 --> 20:30.129 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And they didn't do so.

20:30.162 --> 20:33.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I think it is real
disappointment for
those who have been seeking to
do this for

20:33.966 --> 20:35.734 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
some time.

20:35.768 --> 20:37.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we will have to see what
happens next,
but it appears as though health
care is off

20:37.870 --> 20:39.438 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the table for some period of
time.

20:39.472 --> 20:42.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And I want to ask
you about
that, but what about the
president?

20:42.241 --> 20:47.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president's comment is that
this is all
due to the Democrats, not
Republicans.

20:47.780 --> 20:50.316 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LANHEE CHEN: Well, Democrats
certainly weren't
helpful.

20:50.349 --> 20:53.486 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They didn't participate in the
process, obviously.

20:53.519 --> 20:57.456 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, from the Republican
perspective, there
were a lot of people here that
appeared to

20:57.490 --> 20:59.892 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
say they wanted a perfect piece
of legislation.

20:59.925 --> 21:04.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it seems to me that they
allowed the perfect
to be the enemy of the good in
this case,

21:04.396 --> 21:08.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that there were a lot of things
about this
legislation that would have
moved the ball

21:08.067 --> 21:12.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
forward, for example, on reform
of Medicaid,
which is a huge entitlement
program.

21:12.138 --> 21:15.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If they had actually voted for
the bill, they
would have been moving forward
that effort.

21:15.608 --> 21:19.111 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Instead, it seems to me, there
are some Republicans
that stood in the way.

21:19.145 --> 21:22.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, as I said, I really see
this as a self-inflicted
wound more than anything else.

21:22.348 --> 21:24.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, what do you
think should
happen next?

21:24.517 --> 21:28.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, the president is saying
-- we heard
this from what he told to --
told Robert Costa

21:28.621 --> 21:29.622 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with The Washington Post.

21:29.655 --> 21:33.025 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said, I'm moving on to tax
reform.

21:33.058 --> 21:35.828 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LANHEE CHEN: It's going to be a
challenge.

21:35.861 --> 21:40.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As Speaker Ryan said today, not
being able
to get this done, I think, does
make tax reform

21:40.499 --> 21:42.234 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
harder.

21:42.268 --> 21:45.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it is probably wise to
move on to
a different subject for some
period of time.

21:45.437 --> 21:49.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is clear that there are
divisions within
the Republican Party, Judy,
about how to handle

21:49.508 --> 21:51.844 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
health care and health care
reform going forward.

21:51.877 --> 21:59.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I do think this notion that
Obamacare is going
to collapse in one, large giant
flame is probably

21:59.151 --> 22:00.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
simply inaccurate.

22:00.986 --> 22:04.256 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it's the case that, in
many markets,
you are going to see significant
issues, but

22:04.290 --> 22:06.358 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Medicaid expansion will
continue.

22:06.392 --> 22:08.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Obamacare will, by and
large, continue
as well.

22:08.694 --> 22:12.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think we need to take a
step back, take
stock of what's going to happen,
and hopefully

22:12.998 --> 22:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
return to this issue at some
point in the
future.

22:14.833 --> 22:17.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, it's
interesting you
should say that, because I'm
looking at what

22:17.369 --> 22:20.339 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the president said when he
talked to the press
a short time ago.

22:20.372 --> 22:21.974 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He said what you just said.

22:22.007 --> 22:24.843 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He predicted that it will
collapse.

22:24.877 --> 22:29.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he said, at that point,
Democrats are
going to come crawling back, in
so many words,

22:29.215 --> 22:31.483 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
looking for a way to work with
Republicans.

22:31.517 --> 22:35.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But you're saying that your view
of this whole
thing is different.

22:35.454 --> 22:37.256 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LANHEE CHEN: Yes.

22:37.289 --> 22:40.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, I think, more than
anything, Judy,
I would call this kind of a
slow-motion train

22:40.326 --> 22:46.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wreck more than a significant
sort of single
implosion or single situation
where the bill

22:46.098 --> 22:49.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
completely -- where Obamacare
completely goes
down in flames.

22:49.335 --> 22:52.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it's the case there are
some markets
where there's significant
difficulty.

22:52.471 --> 22:56.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There will be additional markets
where there
will be even more difficulty as
we get toward

22:56.542 --> 22:59.545 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the end of 2017 into 2018.

22:59.578 --> 23:03.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But something like the Medicaid
expansion,
that will continue, and that
will continue

23:03.249 --> 23:06.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to place pressure on the federal
budget, as
well as on state budgets.

23:06.185 --> 23:11.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, if you're
saying it's not
a good idea for Republicans to
come back to

23:11.857 --> 23:14.760 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this issue right now, what
happens to it?

23:14.793 --> 23:16.528 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Where do you see this going?

23:16.562 --> 23:19.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LANHEE CHEN: Well, I do think,
as I said,
in certain markets, you are
going to see,

23:19.765 --> 23:22.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
particularly on the individual
market side
and Obamacare exchanges, you are
going to

23:22.801 --> 23:25.871 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
see continuing declines if
insurer participation.

23:25.904 --> 23:29.141 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do think premiums continue to
go up in some
markets.

23:29.174 --> 23:33.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think there will need to
be efforts
made to look at how to repair
the individual

23:33.379 --> 23:36.181 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
market and to shore up that part
of this.

23:36.215 --> 23:40.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But if we want to go toward
larger system
change, toward entitlement
reform, et cetera,

23:40.586 --> 23:42.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that's going to have to be a
completely different
discussion.

23:42.521 --> 23:46.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it is going to be something
that Republicans
have to get on the same page on
first before

23:46.759 --> 23:48.427 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that ball gets moved forward.

23:48.460 --> 23:51.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And how long does
it take until
you see Republicans getting
there?

23:51.830 --> 23:56.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LANHEE CHEN: Well, I thought --
I had hoped
they would have been able to get
there hopefully

23:56.201 --> 23:58.704 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over the last few weeks, but
that obviously
didn't happen.

23:58.737 --> 24:02.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it's something where
they're going
to have to revisit this issue
after dealing

24:02.541 --> 24:07.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more seriously with whether it's
tax reform
or infrastructure spending or
some other issue

24:07.446 --> 24:11.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be able to demonstrate that
they can govern
and then hopefully come back to
this issue

24:11.617 --> 24:12.751 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as time goes on.

24:12.785 --> 24:15.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lanhee Chen, we
thank you very
much.

24:15.487 --> 24:18.824 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LANHEE CHEN: Thank you.

24:18.857 --> 24:32.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The drama on
Capitol Hill today
wasn't just on the health care
front.

24:32.504 --> 24:37.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
